thread.title: Brazil's Rousseff says looking at ways to open economy
thread.title_full: Brazil's Rousseff says looking at ways to open economy | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: Brazil's Rousseff says looking at ways to open economy
text:
Oct 9 Brazil's President Dilma Rousseff said on Friday she believes the country's economy is still too closed to foreign trade and that her government is looking at ways to open it to other countries.
In a speech to business leaders in Bogota during an official visit to Colombia, Rousseff said expanding trade with South American nations would be a natural course for Brazil, because countries in the region share characteristics that favor integration.
(Reporting by Marcelo Teixeira; Editing by Chizu Nomiyama )
